content: No, Jorge Luis Borges did not write a story named "The Disk." While Borges was a prolific writer of short stories, essays, and poetry, there is no record of him having written a story with this title. Some of Borges' most famous stories include "The Library of Babel," "The Aleph," and "The Garden of Forking Paths." If you have more information about the story you're thinking of, I may be able to help you identify its author.
